Class Requirements

The Lift class SHOULD HAVE ZERO STATES
THERE SHOULD BE NO STATE MACHINE IN LIFT

Control System Requirements:
- Need gravity feedforward model (assume that effect of gravity is constant)
- Need friction feedforward model; don't forget that frictional forces are always applied opposite to your direction of motion
- Need PID feedback

Static variables:
????
I won't say because it depends on the control system you design

Instance data:
- liftMotor
- telemetry
- targetPos
- anything else necessary for your control system

The Lift class should have a constructor taking in HardwareMap and Telemetry
It should:
- initialize the liftMotor
- store telemetry as instance data
- declare anything else necessary for your control system

It should have an update function (takes 0 parameters)
- Inside here, you should write your control algorithm
- You should set the motor power to the output of your algorithm
- Add telemetry calls for debugging

It should have a setTargetPos function
- takes in 1 argument (double targetPos)
- sets target pos of lift to argument

CHALLENGE*****
Assume that the string tension in your lift is affecting its stability
You cannot have 1 single kG value anymore; you need different values based on the lift's current height

Task:
Create an InterpLUT (datatype for an interpolated lookup table):
- input is lift position
- output is a custom tuned kG (you won't actually tune these values, in this hypothetical, you will tune them later)